# Package Management Guidelines

## Always Use Bun
**IMPORTANT**: Always use Bun instead of npm for all package management and script execution in this project.

## Commands
- `bun install` - Install dependencies
- `bun add <package>` - Add new dependencies  
- `bun add -d <package>` - Add dev dependencies
- `bun remove <package>` - Remove dependencies
- `bun run <script>` - Run package.json scripts
- `bun run dev` - Start development server
- `bun run build` - Build the project
- `bun run test` - Run tests
- `bun run test:component` - Run component tests
- `bun run test:e2e` - Run E2E tests

## Why Bun?
- Faster package installation and script execution
- Better TypeScript support out of the box
- Compatible with npm packages and package.json
- Improved performance for development workflows

## Lock File
- Use `bun.lockb` (Bun's lock file) instead of `package-lock.json`
- Commit `bun.lockb` to version control
- Never mix npm and bun in the same project

## Documentation and Examples
- Always use `bun` commands in README files
- Update any documentation that references npm commands
- Use `bun` in CI/CD scripts and deployment instructions